Hungary Passes Law Imposing Tax on Salt, Sugar in Food and Drink

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-07-12T06:41:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/hungary-passes-law-imposing-tax-on-salt-sugar-in-food-and-drink.html
Hungarian lawmakers approved
legislation to curb consumption of salt, sugar and caffeine by
adding taxes on pre-packaged snacks and soft drinks.  The taxes increase from as little as 5 forint per liter
soft drinks to 200 forint ($1.04) per kilogram salted snacks.  The law was approved late yesterday, according to the
parliament  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
 agergely@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  